Package hrps.boundary

Class ServiceUI

  • java.lang.Object
    • hrps.boundary.ServiceUI
  • public class ServiceUI
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is used for displaying UI for displaying and updating room service menu, making orders as well as checking and updating the status of the orders.
    Author:
    An Ruyi, Peng Wenxuan

      • checkOrder

        private void checkOrder()
        Display the UI to read a room number from user, if no such room exists or such room is not valid for room service, display a message and return. If such room is valid for room service, display all the orders made to that room and display the UI for user to update status of any order in those orders.

      • getLegalOrderStatus

        private OrderStatus getLegalOrderStatus()
        Iteratively ask user to enter a valid new status of order as an integer choice from a list of status.
        Returns:
        The OrderStatus parsed from user's input.

      • getLegalOrderNumber

        private int getLegalOrderNumber​(int maxCount)
        Iteratively ask user to choose a valid order number.
        Parameters:
        maxCount - The total number of orders.
        Returns:
        The order number parsed from user's input.

      • makeOrder

        private void makeOrder()
        Display the UI to make an order. If the menu is empty, display a message and return. Order can only be made if a room with the entered room number exists and is OCCUPIED. If the room is valid for making order, display the menu and display the UI for choosing menu items, each with a quantity, and finally the order's remarks. If user does not choose any items, no order is created and a message is displayed. If an order is created, display a successful message.

      • getValidQuantity

        private int getValidQuantity()
        Iteratively ask user to enter a valid quantity of a menu item, which is defined as a positive integer.
        Returns:
        The quantity of a menu item, which is a positive integer.

      • removeMenuItem

        private void removeMenuItem()
        Remove an item from the menu if such item with the entered name exists, otherwise display an error message.

      • updateMenuItem

        private void updateMenuItem()
        Display the UI for user to enter a item name to update its details, including name, description and price. New name is a String and cannot not be the same as another item's name in the menu, price must be a non-negative double.

      • createMenuItem

        private void createMenuItem()
        Display the UI for user to enter name (cannot be duplicated), description and price (cannot be negative) for a new menu item and create that item.
